defs.docs: Compile-time generated maps and sets.

defs.name: map
defs.docs: An immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: Map
defs.docs: An immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Map` is empty.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of entries in the `Map`.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Determines if `key` is in the `Map`.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value that `key` maps to.

defs.name: get_key
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the map's internal static instance of the given
 key.

defs.name: get_entry
defs.docs: Like `get`, but returns both the key and the value.

defs.name: entries
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the key/value pairs in the map.

defs.name: keys
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the keys in the map.

defs.name: values
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the values in the map.

defs.name: Entries
defs.docs: An iterator over the key/value pairs in a `Map`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys in a `Map`.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `Map`.

defs.name: set
defs.docs: An immutable set constructed at compile time.

defs.name: Set
defs.docs: An immutable set constructed at compile time.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the `Set`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Set` contains no elements.

defs.name: get_key
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the set's internal static instance of the given
 key.

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns true if `value` is in the `Set`.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the values in the set.

defs.name: is_disjoint
defs.docs: Returns true if `other` shares no elements with `self`.

defs.name: is_subset
defs.docs: Returns true if `other` contains all values in `self`.

defs.name: is_superset
defs.docs: Returns true if `self` contains all values in `other`.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `Set`.

defs.name: ordered_map
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: OrderedMap
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable map constructed at compile time.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of entries in the `Map`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the `Map` is empty.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value that `key` maps to.

defs.name: get_key
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the map's internal static instance of the given
 key.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Determines if `key` is in the `Map`.

defs.name: get_index
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the key within the list used to initialize
 the ordered map.

defs.name: index
defs.docs:
Returns references to both the key and values at an index
 within the list used to initialize the ordered map. See `.get_index(key)`.

defs.name: get_entry
defs.docs: Like `get`, but returns both the key and the value.

defs.name: entries
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the key/value pairs in the map.

defs.name: keys
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the keys in the map.

defs.name: values
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the values in the map.

defs.name: Entries
defs.docs: An iterator over the entries in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `OrderedMap`.

defs.name: ordered_set
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable set constructed at compile time.

defs.name: OrderedSet
defs.docs: An order-preserving immutable set constructed at compile time.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the `OrderedSet`.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the `OrderedSet` contains no elements.

defs.name: get_key
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the set's internal static instance of the given
 key.

defs.name: get_index
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the key within the list used to initialize
 the ordered set.

defs.name: index
defs.docs:
Returns a reference to the key at an index
 within the list used to initialize the ordered set. See `.get_index(key)`.

defs.name: contains
defs.docs: Returns true if `value` is in the `Set`.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the values in the set.

defs.name: is_disjoint
defs.docs: Returns true if `other` shares no elements with `self`.

defs.name: is_subset
defs.docs: Returns true if `other` contains all values in `self`.

defs.name: is_superset
defs.docs: Returns true if `self` contains all values in `other`.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the values in a `OrderedSet`.
